1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:07,000
A lump can look identical on the surface—
and be completely different underneath.

2
00:00:07,000 --> 00:00:18,000
After dealing with cyst-related issues myself, I wanted the health explainer I wish I had:
visual, private, multilingual, and honest about uncertainty. So I built LumpMap 3D.

3
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:27,000
It starts with location. The interactive 3D atlas maps seventeen body regions,
front and back, and works with an accessible region list.

4
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:33,000
Select the top of the buttock cleft,
and it surfaces patterns worth learning about.

5
00:00:33,000 --> 00:00:40,000
Then it changes scale—from the body
to what may be happening beneath the skin.

6
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:58,000
Here, pilonidal disease is not presented as just another cyst. Three procedural cutaways show a normal cleft,
a pit and sinus tract, and an inflamed stage, alongside care guidance and source-linked facts.

7
00:00:58,000 --> 00:01:09,000
Comparison mode holds scale constant, making a pilonidal sinus,
a boil, and a true epidermoid cyst visually distinct.

8
00:01:09,000 --> 00:01:16,000
But people rarely describe health concerns
in clinical language.

9
00:01:16,000 --> 00:01:26,000
A user can write in English, Urdu, or Roman Urdu. With a server key,
GPT-5.6 converts everyday language into a strict Structured Output schema.

10
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:36,000
The public demo also keeps a local fallback,
so the experience remains testable without exposing a key.

11
00:01:36,000 --> 00:01:50,000
The model does not diagnose and cannot choose urgency. Curated local records explain possible patterns,
while the Visit Note includes only facts the user actually supplied.

12
00:01:50,000 --> 00:02:05,000
Safety is deterministic. Severe pain, swelling, fever, or a location directly beside the anus
triggers same-day guidance through local rules. GPT-5.6 cannot downgrade that result.

13
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:12,000
That boundary is deliberate: language understanding on one side;
safety authority on the other.

14
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:24,000
I used Codex as my primary engineering and design collaborator: scaffolding the Next.js app,
building procedural Three.js anatomy, refining accessibility and privacy, and writing fifty-six focused tests.

15
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:28,000
The implementation was developed in this Codex task.

16
00:02:28,000 --> 00:02:38,000
Every lesson shows sources and review dates. There are no accounts,
trackers, uploads, or saved health histories.

17
00:02:38,000 --> 00:02:48,000
LumpMap 3D does not tell people what they have.
It helps them see what differs, what matters, and when to seek care.
